        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-14T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-14T10:00:00-05:00" n="831"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d831">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War 1939/795: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-14T18:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 14, 1941—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:53 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>949. My 944, July 13, 2 p.m. I am informed that agreement has been reached on the
                    points in the armistice terms which the British found unacceptable and that
                    formal signature has taken place. The text of the revised terms has not yet been
                    received here but it is expected that it will become available in the course of
                    the day and that it may be possible to make it public tonight.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
